Falun Gong practitioners and supporters rallied in front of the Customs House building in downtown Sydney on January 31, 2020. They wanted to raise awareness of the persecution of the spiritual group in China and to celebrate the 350 million Chinese people who have withdrawn from the Communist Party (CCP) and its affiliated organizations.

The day of activities started with practitioners demonstrating the five sets of exercises on the plaza in front of the customs building in the early morning and was followed by a rally and speeches.

Due to the outbreak of the coronavirus in China, fewer Chinese tourists have been coming to this popular tourist site. Some Chinese tourists were still around, though, and they listened to the speeches at the rally and took fliers. Some said they would quit the communist party online.

A Chinese Australian came to the rally and gave an impromptu speech after reading an announcement about the event in the Epoch Times.

Chinese Australian: I want to express my respect to the Falun Gong group!

snippet.textDisplay:
I hope this is constructive criticism rather then nagging but, I feel the way Mark acted in this video a little less then desirable. Ethan of course had his moments too, but not to the extent Mark did.

For me, when getting taught about something as dangerous as a deadly weapon I felt that they should have focused more on concentrating and listening to the right way to do things. Being misinformed could potentially lead to misfiring on themselves or someone else. I think that's why the woman got so fed up with it.

Also, it was kind of distressing to see Mark nagging on Ethan, you could tell he was trying to be respectful and started to get frustrated. That's why he said "don't touch me". I could be misinterpreting but I think there was genuine emotion in that response and not just a joke, but I could be wrong. I've always felt a bit frustrated by the way they've been interrupting the people that have been teaching them in these past videos. I know that they are a comedy channel and I completely understand that's why they do this, but there has to be a line there. Maybe next time they could test out toning it down just a bit.
